# Source to Client and Contract Sync

When changes are made to the main code in `src/`, keep both client implementations and contract tests aligned with the new API/spec behavior.

## Required updates

1. If API endpoints are added or changed, update the client library in `client/`.
2. Keep the Node.js mirror implementation in `client/` aligned with the main implementation.
3. If behavior/spec changes are relevant, update contract tests in `client/test/` so both implementations are validated against the same expectations.

## Completion checklist

- [ ] `client/` updated for endpoint/API changes
- [ ] Node.js mirror implementation updated to match main behavior
- [ ] `client/test/` contract tests updated when behavior/spec changed
